---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Editorial Policy" 
  description="Our editorial standards, content review process, and commitment to accuracy at Exotic Pet Atlas."
  keywords="editorial policy, content standards, accuracy, review process, expert verification"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Editorial Policy</h1>
    
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        At Exotic Pet Atlas, we maintain rigorous editorial standards to ensure that all information published on our platform is accurate, current, and helpful to our readers. This policy outlines our content creation, review, and update processes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Content Creation Standards</h2>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-pastel-blue mb-3">Expert Review</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        All pet care and medical content is reviewed by licensed veterinarians specializing in exotic animal medicine or certified exotic animal specialists. We prioritize reviewers with:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Board certification from the American Board of Veterinary Practitioners (ABVP) in exotic companion mammals, avian practice, or reptile/amphibian practice</li>
        <li>Minimum 5 years of clinical experience with exotic animals</li>
        <li>Active veterinary licenses in good standing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-pastel-blue mb-3">Legal Information</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        State law information is sourced exclusively from:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
        <li>Official state statutes and administrative codes</li>
        <li>State wildlife and fish & game department regulations</li>
        <li>County and municipal ordinances (where applicable)</li>
        <li>Official government websites and publications</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Legal information is for educational purposes only and does not constitute legal advice. Laws change frequently - always verify current regulations with your local authorities.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Source Requirements</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">We classify sources into tiers:</p>
      
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Tier 1 (Primary Sources)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Peer-reviewed veterinary journals, official government regulations, board-certified specialists</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Tier 2 (Secondary Sources)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Veterinary textbooks, established organizations (ARAV, AEMV), university extension publications</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-yellow-500 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Tier 3 (Supplementary)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Experienced breeder input, community best practices (clearly labeled as such)</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Update Schedule</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-pastel-green mb-2">Legal Content</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">Reviewed: <strong>Monthly</strong></p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">State laws and regulations are checked monthly for legislative changes, new permits, or updated restrictions.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-pastel-pink mb-2">Care Guides</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">Reviewed: <strong>Quarterly</strong></p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Pet care information is reviewed quarterly to incorporate new research and updated veterinary recommendations.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-pastel-blue mb-2">Veterinary Directories</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">Reviewed: <strong>Bi-annually</strong></p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Vet listings verified twice yearly; user-reported changes updated within 7 days.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-pastel-purple mb-2">Setup Guides</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">Reviewed: <strong>Annually</strong></p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Equipment recommendations updated as new products and technologies become available.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Corrections Policy</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        We take accuracy seriously. If you identify an error or outdated information:
      </p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Submit corrections via our <a href="/contact/" class="text-pastel-blue hover:underline">contact form</a></li>
        <li>Include specific page URL and source documentation</li>
        <li>We review all submissions within 48 hours</li>
        <li>Verified corrections are updated within 7 days</li>
        <li>Major corrections include an update notice on the affected page</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Conflicts of Interest</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        Exotic Pet Atlas operates independently. We disclose:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>All affiliate relationships are clearly marked</li>
        <li>Veterinary clinic listings are informational only (no paid placements)</li>
        <li>Breeder directories do not constitute endorsements</li>
        <li>Product recommendations are based on veterinary standards, not sponsorships</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-pastel-beige rounded-lg p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Commitment to Transparency</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        We believe in transparent communication with our readers. All content includes clear source attributions, last-updated dates, and expert reviewer credentials where applicable. Our goal is not just to inform, but to empower you to verify and validate the information we provide.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-8 text-center">
      Last updated: January 2026
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
